  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;
  mso-no-proof:yes'>Resort Bases are specialized state-owned bases built at
  scenic locations throughout the galaxy. These are favored vacation
  destinations for tourists.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;
  mso-no-proof:yes'>Construction ships build resort bases at any location
  deemed scenic enough. These locations could be ringed planets, unusual go=
ld
  or crystal asteroids, black holes, neutron stars, or planets with unusual
  ruins or ancient monuments.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;
  mso-no-proof:yes'>Passenger liner ships transport tourists from wealthy
  colonies to resort bases. As tourists arrive at the resort, the empire th=
at
  owns the resort earns income. Tourists will only choose to visit resorts
  where the scenery is sufficiently appealing. They also don&#8217;t like to
  travel too far. So build your resort bases at the most scenic locations t=
hat
  are reasonably close to large, wealthy colonies.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;
  mso-no-proof:yes'>Resort bases are typically lightly armed and defended, =
with
  enough firepower to fend off any marauding pirates or stray space creatur=
es.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
